📓 JOURNAL ACCESS MODEL (ADMIN-ONLY)

The journal repository is private and admin-only.

Rules:
- Protected by admin authentication (middleware)
- Uses a dedicated server-side GitHub token
- Does NOT use Redis
- Does NOT consume quota
- Does NOT use session locking
- GitHub private repo access is the enforcement boundary

Rationale:
The journal is a single-user, trusted workflow. Quota and session locks are unnecessary
and intentionally bypassed to avoid backend exhaustion.


🔑 GITHUB TOKEN STRATEGY

GITHUB_TOKEN
- Used by /api/markdown
- Subject to Redis quota & session enforcement
- Intended for public or semi-public access

GITHUB_JOURNAL_TOKEN
- Used only by /api/journal
- Admin-only
- Private repo access
- No Redis, no quota, no session logic
- Separate blast radius and rotation lifecycle



🧠 TOKEN META (REDIS)

token:<token>:meta {
  name
  quotaScope        // session | token
  resetPolicy       // daily | never
  limit
  enabled
  createdAt
}


🧠 SESSION LOCK (ANTI-SHARING)

token:<token>:active_session = <sessionId>

TTL-based sliding lock  
Same session refreshes TTL  
Different session → BLOCKED (TOKEN_IN_USE)  


📊 QUOTA SYSTEM (CRITICAL)

quota:<scope>:<date | lifetime>

Where scope is:
session:<sessionId>  
token:<token>  

Rules:
Checked BEFORE GitHub fetch  
Consumed ONLY AFTER successful fetch  
Daily quotas expire via TTL  
Lifetime quotas never expire  


